************** G E N E R A L   I N F O R M A T I O N *************2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
This evaluated data file is based on a software system built      2046 1451
around the nuclear model code TALYS [kon07], version 1.74. It is  2046 1451
part of a large collection of isotopic evaluations, all created by2046 1451
running the system with either adjusted or default input          2046 1451
parameters. This means that the data in the entire collection have2046 1451
been tested in detail for many isotopes against individual        2046 1451
experimental data, while for other isotopes it is only as good as 2046 1451
the global quality of TALYS at the moment. The mutual quality of  2046 1451
all individual data files is however consistent: The same set of  2046 1451
nuclear models is used and, equally important, the same ENDF-6    2046 1451
formatting procedures for each isotope. The data file has been    2046 1451
created automatically using the ENDF-6 format generator TEFAL.    2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
The resulting data file provides a complete representation of     2046 1451
nuclear data needed for transport, activation, damage, heating,   2046 1451
radioactivity, and shielding applications over the incident       2046 1451
neutron energy range from 1.e-11 to 200. MeV.                     2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
All transport and activation data for neutrons, charged particles,2046 1451
photons and residual nuclides are filed. This includes cross      2046 1451
sections, angular distributions, double-differential spectra,     2046 1451
isomeric production, discrete and continuum photon production     2046 1451
cross sections, residual production cross sections and recoils.   2046 1451
This general purpose evaluation can thus be used as both          2046 1451
transport and activation library.                                 2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
A complete set of covariance data is included, which is stored    2046 1451
in MF31-40.                                                       2046 1451
