***************************** T A L Y S **************************2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
TALYS is a computer code system for the prediction and analysis   2046 1451
of nuclear reactions. TALYS simulates reactions that involve      2046 1451
neutrons, gamma-rays, protons, deuterons, tritons, helions and    2046 1451
alpha-particles, in the 1 keV - 200 MeV energy range. This is     2046 1451
achieved by implementing a suite of nuclear reaction models into  2046 1451
a single code system. This nuclear data file is based on a        2046 1451
theoretical analysis that utilizes the optical model, compound    2046 1451
nucleus statistical theory, fission, direct reactions and         2046 1451
pre-equilibrium processes, in combination with databases and      2046 1451
models for nuclear structure. The following output of TALYS is    2046 1451
stored in this data file:                                         2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
- Total, elastic and non-elastic cross sections                   2046 1451
- Inelastic cross sections to discrete states                     2046 1451
- Exclusive channel cross sections, e.g. (n,g), (n,2n), (n,np),.. 2046 1451
- Inelastic scattering angular distributions to discrete states   2046 1451
- Exclusive channel energy spectra                                2046 1451
- Exclusive channel double-differential spectra                   2046 1451
- Exclusive gamma production for discrete states and continuum    2046 1451
- Elastic scattering angular distributions                        2046 1451
- Recoil data                                                     2046 1451
- Total particle cross sections, e.g. (n,xn), (n,xp),..           2046 1451
- Total particle energy spectra                                   2046 1451
- Total particle double-differential spectra                      2046 1451
- Isomeric and ground state cross sections                        2046 1451
- Residual production cross sections                              2046 1451
                                                                  2046 1451
For a description of the used nuclear models and their            2046 1451
parameterization we refer to [kon12]. If for this specific        2046 1451
nuclide we deviate from the global parameterization, it is made   2046 1451
explicit above under Nuclide Specific Information.                2046 1451
